<subSubSection id="8A846530544BA57EFF6C07DE455CFECC" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="512" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C22136BB544BA57EFF6C07DE455CFECC" blockId="16.[151,1436,1927,2024]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="512" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis id="F0EAEAA9544BA57FFF6C07DE465FF837" bold="true" box="[199,321,1963,1988]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Size 
<quantity id="05669B5E544BA57FFE2C07D9451DF837" box="[391,515,1964,1989]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" unit="mm" value="38.0" valueMax="56.0" valueMin="20.0">20â€“56 mm</quantity>
by 
<quantity id="05669B5E544BA57FFD9E07D945B3F837" box="[565,685,1964,1989]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">
1.5â€“ 
<quantity id="05669B5E544BA57FFDCD07D945B3F837" box="[614,685,1964,1989]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
</quantity>
. Segment numbers 77â€“115. Color of live specimens light red to reddish white. Male pores paired in XVIII, on a relatively large porophore. Post-clitellar genital markings unpaired, small mid-ventral tubercles, pre-setal on some of XVII, XIXâ€“XXI. Spermathecal pores paired in 5/6 or absent. Preclitellar genital markings paired small pre-setal tubercles on some of Vâ€“VIII. Female pore single in XIV. First dorsal pore 11/12 or 12/13. Spermathecae present or absent; when present, one pair or single in VI, large. Prostate glands present or absent; when present, large, extending through some or all of XVIâ€“XXIII. Intestinal caeca simple, extending anteriorly to XXIII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8A846530544AA57EFF6C0139444EFE5E" pageId="17" pageNumber="512" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C22136BB544AA57EFF6C0139444EFE5E" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="17" pageNumber="512">
<materialsCitation id="72F63CE6544AA57EFF6C0139444EFE5E" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1324406314" country="United States of America" location="Louisiana" pageId="17" pageNumber="512" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Louisiana">
<emphasis id="F0EAEAA9544AA57EFF6C01394625FE97" bold="true" box="[199,315,332,356]" pageId="17" pageNumber="512">Remarks.</emphasis>
Easily distinguished from most pheretimoid species by its body size, 
<taxonomicName id="059E4D38544AA57EFBD3013943E4FE97" box="[1144,1274,332,356]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Amynthas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="17" pageNumber="512" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="minimus">
<emphasis id="F0EAEAA9544AA57EFBD3013943E4FE97" box="[1144,1274,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="512">A. minimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the smallest pheretimoid earthworms in the world. It was first recorded in the continental 
<collectingCountry id="BA89762B544AA57EFBD4010543BDFE7B" box="[1151,1187,368,392]" name="United States of America" pageId="17" pageNumber="512">US</collectingCountry>
in 
<quantity id="05669B5E544AA57EFB67011A423AFE7B" box="[1228,1316,367,392]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.00126" pageId="17" pageNumber="512" unit="in" value="1969.0">1969 in</quantity>
<collectingRegion id="005AF859544AA57EFA85011A4282FE7B" box="[1326,1436,367,392]" country="United States of America" name="Louisiana" pageId="17" pageNumber="512">Louisiana</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A60F4B4A544AA57EFF3501E1463DFE5F" author="Gates" box="[158,291,404,428]" pageId="17" pageNumber="512" refString="Gates, G. E. (1982) Farewell to North American megadriles. Megadrilogica, 4, 12 - 77." type="journal article" year="1982">Gates 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Reproduction of this species is parthenogenetic.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
